{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":811,"text":"We've evolved with tools,\nand tools have evolved with us."},{"time":4388,"text":"Our ancestors created these\nhand axes 1.5 million years ago,"},{"time":9431,"text":"shaping them to not only\nfit the task at hand"},{"time":12477,"text":"but also their hand."}]},{"cues":[{"time":14747,"text":"However, over the years,"},{"time":16351,"text":"tools have become\nmore and more specialized."},{"time":19293,"text":"These sculpting tools\nhave evolved through their use,"},{"time":23154,"text":"and each one has a different form\nwhich matches its function."},{"time":26740,"text":"And they leverage\nthe dexterity of our hands"},{"time":29432,"text":"in order to manipulate things\nwith much more precision."},{"time":33338,"text":"But as tools have become\nmore and more complex,"},{"time":36428,"text":"we need more complex controls\nto control them."},{"time":40714,"text":"And so designers have become\nvery adept at creating interfaces"},{"time":45182,"text":"that allow you to manipulate parameters\nwhile you're attending to other things,"},{"time":48944,"text":"such as taking a photograph\nand changing the focus"},{"time":51847,"text":"or the aperture."}]},{"cues":[{"time":53918,"text":"But the computer has fundamentally\nchanged the way we think about tools"},{"time":58161,"text":"because computation is dynamic."},{"time":60564,"text":"So it can do a million different things"},{"time":62739,"text":"and run a million different applications."},{"time":65112,"text":"However, computers have\nthe same static physical form"},{"time":68881,"text":"for all of these different applications"},{"time":70841,"text":"and the same static\ninterface elements as well."},{"time":73976,"text":"And I believe that this\nis fundamentally a problem,"},{"time":76420,"text":"because it doesn't really allow us\nto interact with our hands"},{"time":79440,"text":"and capture the rich dexterity\nthat we have in our bodies."},{"time":84026,"text":"And my belief is that, then,\nwe must need new types of interfaces"},{"time":88586,"text":"that can capture these\nrich abilities that we have"},{"time":92369,"text":"and that can physically adapt to us"},{"time":94763,"text":"and allow us to interact in new ways."},{"time":97037,"text":"And so that's what I've been doing\nat the MIT Media Lab"},{"time":99648,"text":"and now at Stanford."}]},{"cues":[{"time":101901,"text":"So with my colleagues,\nDaniel Leithinger and Hiroshi Ishii,"},{"time":105536,"text":"we created inFORM,"},{"time":106949,"text":"where the interface can actually\ncome off the screen"},{"time":109471,"text":"and you can physically manipulate it."},{"time":111771,"text":"Or you can visualize\n3D information physically"},{"time":114538,"text":"and touch it and feel it\nto understand it in new ways."},{"time":123889,"text":"Or you can interact through gestures\nand direct deformations"},{"time":127989,"text":"to sculpt digital clay."},{"time":134474,"text":"Or interface elements can arise\nout of the surface"},{"time":137579,"text":"and change on demand."},{"time":138975,"text":"And the idea is that for each\nindividual application,"},{"time":141507,"text":"the physical form can be matched\nto the application."},{"time":145196,"text":"And I believe this represents a new way"},{"time":147325,"text":"that we can interact with information,"},{"time":149299,"text":"by making it physical."}]},{"cues":[{"time":151142,"text":"So the question is, how can we use this?"},{"time":153810,"text":"Traditionally, urban planners\nand architects build physical models"},{"time":157524,"text":"of cities and buildings\nto better understand them."},{"time":160358,"text":"So with Tony Tang at the Media Lab,\nwe created an interface built on inFORM"},{"time":164597,"text":"to allow urban planners\nto design and view entire cities."},{"time":169604,"text":"And now you can walk around it,\nbut it's dynamic, it's physical,"},{"time":173885,"text":"and you can also interact directly."},{"time":175609,"text":"Or you can look at different views,"},{"time":177371,"text":"such as population or traffic information,"},{"time":180212,"text":"but it's made physical."}]},{"cues":[{"time":182996,"text":"We also believe that these dynamic\nshape displays can really change"},{"time":186830,"text":"the ways that we remotely\ncollaborate with people."},{"time":189814,"text":"So when we're working together in person,"},{"time":192141,"text":"I'm not only looking at your face"},{"time":193823,"text":"but I'm also gesturing\nand manipulating objects,"},{"time":196885,"text":"and that's really hard to do\nwhen you're using tools like Skype."},{"time":201905,"text":"And so using inFORM,\nyou can reach out from the screen"},{"time":204915,"text":"and manipulate things at a distance."},{"time":207051,"text":"So we used the pins of the display\nto represent people's hands,"},{"time":210250,"text":"allowing them to actually touch\nand manipulate objects at a distance."},{"time":218519,"text":"And you can also manipulate\nand collaborate on 3D data sets as well,"},{"time":222817,"text":"so you can gesture around them\nas well as manipulate them."},{"time":226510,"text":"And that allows people to collaborate\non these new types of 3D information"},{"time":230924,"text":"in a richer way than might\nbe possible with traditional tools."},{"time":235870,"text":"And so you can also\nbring in existing objects,"},{"time":238647,"text":"and those will be captured on one side\nand transmitted to the other."},{"time":241885,"text":"Or you can have an object that's linked\nbetween two places,"},{"time":244695,"text":"so as I move a ball on one side,"},{"time":246803,"text":"the ball moves on the other as well."},{"time":250278,"text":"And so we do this by capturing\nthe remote user"},{"time":253405,"text":"using a depth-sensing camera\nlike a Microsoft Kinect."}]},{"cues":[{"time":256758,"text":"Now, you might be wondering\nhow does this all work,"},{"time":259799,"text":"and essentially, what it is,\nis 900 linear actuators"},{"time":263474,"text":"that are connected to these\nmechanical linkages"},{"time":265784,"text":"that allow motion down here\nto be propagated in these pins above."},{"time":269554,"text":"So it's not that complex\ncompared to what's going on at CERN,"},{"time":273145,"text":"but it did take a long time\nfor us to build it."},{"time":275495,"text":"And so we started with a single motor,"},{"time":277774,"text":"a single linear actuator,"},{"time":279816,"text":"and then we had to design\na custom circuit board to control them."},{"time":283003,"text":"And then we had to make a lot of them."},{"time":285079,"text":"And so the problem with having\n900 of something"},{"time":288717,"text":"is that you have to do\nevery step 900 times."},{"time":291861,"text":"And so that meant that we had\na lot of work to do."},{"time":294242,"text":"So we sort of set up\na mini-sweatshop in the Media Lab"},{"time":297998,"text":"and brought undergrads in and convinced\nthem to do \"research\" --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":301734,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":302772,"text":"and had late nights\nwatching movies, eating pizza"},{"time":305814,"text":"and screwing in thousands of screws."},{"time":307666,"text":"You know -- research."}]},{"cues":[{"time":308888,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":310459,"text":"But anyway, I think that we were\nreally excited by the things"},{"time":313801,"text":"that inFORM allowed us to do."},{"time":315521,"text":"Increasingly, we're using mobile devices,\nand we interact on the go."},{"time":319745,"text":"But mobile devices, just like computers,"},{"time":322448,"text":"are used for so many\ndifferent applications."},{"time":324783,"text":"So you use them to talk on the phone,"},{"time":326800,"text":"to surf the web, to play games,\nto take pictures"},{"time":329980,"text":"or even a million different things."},{"time":331713,"text":"But again, they have the same\nstatic physical form"},{"time":334721,"text":"for each of these applications."},{"time":336863,"text":"And so we wanted to know how can we take\nsome of the same interactions"},{"time":340250,"text":"that we developed for inFORM"},{"time":341957,"text":"and bring them to mobile devices."}]},{"cues":[{"time":344427,"text":"So at Stanford, we created\nthis haptic edge display,"},{"time":348098,"text":"which is a mobile device\nwith an array of linear actuators"},{"time":351299,"text":"that can change shape,"},{"time":352670,"text":"so you can feel in your hand\nwhere you are as you're reading a book."},{"time":357058,"text":"Or you can feel in your pocket\nnew types of tactile sensations"},{"time":360819,"text":"that are richer than the vibration."},{"time":362645,"text":"Or buttons can emerge from the side\nthat allow you to interact"},{"time":365904,"text":"where you want them to be."},{"time":369334,"text":"Or you can play games\nand have actual buttons."},{"time":373786,"text":"And so we were able to do this"},{"time":375326,"text":"by embedding 40 small, tiny\nlinear actuators inside the device,"},{"time":380104,"text":"and that allow you not only to touch them"},{"time":382183,"text":"but also back-drive them as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":384911,"text":"But we've also looked at other ways\nto create more complex shape change."},{"time":389113,"text":"So we've used pneumatic actuation\nto create a morphing device"},{"time":392529,"text":"where you can go from something\nthat looks a lot like a phone ..."},{"time":396418,"text":"to a wristband on the go."},{"time":399720,"text":"And so together with Ken Nakagaki\nat the Media Lab,"},{"time":402583,"text":"we created this new\nhigh-resolution version"},{"time":405161,"text":"that uses an array of servomotors\nto change from interactive wristband"},{"time":411135,"text":"to a touch-input device"},{"time":414287,"text":"to a phone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":415556,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":418104,"text":"And we're also interested\nin looking at ways"},{"time":420300,"text":"that users can actually\ndeform the interfaces"},{"time":422951,"text":"to shape them into the devices\nthat they want to use."},{"time":425863,"text":"So you can make something\nlike a game controller,"},{"time":428295,"text":"and then the system will understand\nwhat shape it's in"},{"time":430949,"text":"and change to that mode."}]},{"cues":[{"time":434052,"text":"So, where does this point?"},{"time":435648,"text":"How do we move forward from here?"},{"time":437600,"text":"I think, really, where we are today"},{"time":440219,"text":"is in this new age\nof the Internet of Things,"},{"time":442997,"text":"where we have computers everywhere --"},{"time":444812,"text":"they're in our pockets,\nthey're in our walls,"},{"time":446954,"text":"they're in almost every device\nthat you'll buy in the next five years."},{"time":450544,"text":"But what if we stopped\nthinking about devices"},{"time":453449,"text":"and think instead about environments?"},{"time":455867,"text":"And so how can we have smart furniture"},{"time":458403,"text":"or smart rooms or smart environments"},{"time":461743,"text":"or cities that can adapt to us physically,"},{"time":464859,"text":"and allow us to do new ways\nof collaborating with people"},{"time":469114,"text":"and doing new types of tasks?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":471376,"text":"So for the Milan Design Week,\nwe created TRANSFORM,"},{"time":474784,"text":"which is an interactive table-scale\nversion of these shape displays,"},{"time":478632,"text":"which can move physical objects\non the surface; for example,"},{"time":481839,"text":"reminding you to take your keys."},{"time":484120,"text":"But it can also transform\nto fit different ways of interacting."},{"time":488626,"text":"So if you want to work,"},{"time":489967,"text":"then it can change to sort of\nset up your work system."},{"time":492983,"text":"And so as you bring a device over,"},{"time":494958,"text":"it creates all the affordances you need"},{"time":497720,"text":"and brings other objects\nto help you accomplish those goals."}]},{"cues":[{"time":505139,"text":"So, in conclusion,"},{"time":506724,"text":"I really think that we need to think\nabout a new, fundamentally different way"},{"time":510747,"text":"of interacting with computers."},{"time":513551,"text":"We need computers\nthat can physically adapt to us"},{"time":516529,"text":"and adapt to the ways\nthat we want to use them"},{"time":519154,"text":"and really harness the rich dexterity\nthat we have of our hands,"},{"time":523725,"text":"and our ability to think spatially\nabout information by making it physical."},{"time":528663,"text":"But looking forward, I think we need\nto go beyond this, beyond devices,"},{"time":532683,"text":"to really think about new ways\nthat we can bring people together,"},{"time":536100,"text":"and bring our information into the world,"},{"time":539142,"text":"and think about smart environments\nthat can adapt to us physically."},{"time":543119,"text":"So with that, I will leave you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":544707,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":545882,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}